{"title": "Giles Corey of the Salem Farms", "description": "Giles Corey was an English-born farmer who was \"pressed to death\" for refusing to enter a plea during the notorious Salem Witch Trials in 1692. His wife Martha was one of fourteen women hanged after the trials.\r\n\r\nThis verse drama was written in 1868 and published as one of Longfellow's New England Tragedies.\r\n\r\n(Summary by Alan Mapstone)\r\n\r\n<b>Cast List:</b>\r\nPrologue: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/7170\">Alan Mapstone</a>\r\nGiles Corey: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17713\">Brian Fullen</a>\r\nMartha(his wife): <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/19584\">ShrimpPhish</a>\r\nJohn Hathorne(Magistrate): <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/8425\">Larry Wilson</a>\r\nCotton Mather(Minister): <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/8011\">Greg Giordano</a>\r\nJonathan Walcot: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17713\">Brian Fullen</a>\r\nMary Walcot: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/18543\">Agnes Robert Behr</a>\r\nTituba(Indian Woman): <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/7026\">Michele Eaton</a>\r\nJohn Gloyd: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17576\">Beeswaxcandle</a>\r\nRichard Gardner: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/6754\">ToddHW</a>\r\nDeacon: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17384\">Ted Perkins</a>\r\nOne of the Men: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/6754\">ToddHW</a>\r\nFarmer/Boy: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17662\">Inkell</a>\r\nFarmer/Man: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/8011\">Greg Giordano</a>\r\nJailer/Sheriff: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/17662\">Inkell</a>\r\nNarrator/Editor: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/7170\">Alan Mapstone</a>", "duration": 5777, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "43", "name": "Henry Wadsworth Longfellow"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/gilescorey_2505_librivox/giles_corey_2505.jpg", "copyright_year": "1868", "genres": ["Drama"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read b